oaches to the erotic, exploring female sexual subjectivities and destabilizing assumptions about gender. Rachel Middleman reveals these artists' radical interventions in both aesthetic conventions and social norms.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aArt. 4aContemporary (1945-). 4aHistory. 7aART / History / Contemporary (1945-).2bisacsh1 aMiddleman, Rachel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106676770 cprintz978052029458540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052035615340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520356153423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520356153/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles